<h3>Question 5</h3>
<div><p><p>Describe different phases of simulation study with help of flowchart.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>simulation study includes some steps and they are dealt below with a flowchart.</p>
<p><img data-recalc-dims="1" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-39346 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/hamrocsit.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/model-simulation.drawio.png?resize=387%2C1916&#038;ssl=1" alt="- Hamro CSIT" width="387" height="1916" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>fig : flowchart of system study</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li><strong>Problem Formulation:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Clearly define the problem that needs to be addressed using simulation. Identify the objectives and goals of the study.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Setting of Objectives &amp; Overall Project Plan:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Establish specific objectives for the simulation study and create an overall project plan outlining the timeline, resources, and milestones.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Model Conceptualization:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Develop a conceptual model that represents the system being simulated. This involves deciding on the structure and components of the model.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Data Collection:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Gather relevant data to support the model. This includes parameters, inputs, and initial conditions. The data should be accurate and representative of the real system.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Model Translation:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Translate the conceptual model into a formal representation, often using mathematical equations or computational algorithms. Implement the model in a simulation environment.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Verification:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Ensure that the simulation model accurately represents the conceptual model by checking its correctness. Verification involves validating the coding and logic of the model.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Validation:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Validate the simulation model by comparing its outputs to real-world data. This step ensures that the model behaves realistically and provides valid insights into the system.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Experimental Design:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Plan the experiments or scenarios that will be simulated. Define the input variations, conditions, and factors to be tested. Set up the simulation’s boundary conditions.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Production Runs:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Execute the simulation with the specified inputs and conditions. Collect data on the system’s behavior, performance, and other relevant output measures during the production runs.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Repetition of Runs:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Conduct multiple simulation runs to assess the variability and robustness of the model. Repetition helps ensure that the results are consistent and reliable.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Documentation &amp; Report:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Document the simulation study, including the model details, assumptions, data sources, and results. Generate a comprehensive report summarizing the findings and insights.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Implementation:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Implement the recommendations or decisions based on the simulation results. This may involve changes to the real-world system or the adoption of specific strategies.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<h3>Question 6</h3>
<div><p><p>Explain markov chain with suitable example. What are diffrernt application areas of markov chain?</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>If the future states of a process are independent of the past and depend only on the present, the process is called a Markov process. A discrete state Markov process is called a Markov chain. A Markov Chain is a random process with the property that the next state depends only on the current state.</p>
<p>Markov chains are used to analyze trends and predict the future. (Weather, stock market, genetics, product success, etc.</p>
<p><strong>Formally,</strong></p>
<p>A Markov chain is a sequence of random variables X<sub>1</sub>, X<sub>2</sub>, X<sub>3</sub>, … with the Markov property, namely that, given the present state, the future and past states are independent.</p>
